President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Nebraska due to severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from June 17 to July 1, 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Constance C. Johnson-Cage has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.